n \in \mathbb{N}
x^2 + x+ 1\mid x^{2n} + x^n + 1
(x^3 - 1) = (x-1)(x^2 + x+1)
x^3 - 1\mid x^{2n} + x^n + 1
\omega
x^2+x+1=0, \omega^2+\omega+1=0\implies \omega^3=1
3|n, n=3m
\omega^n=\omega^{3m}=(\omega^3)^m=1 \text{ and } \omega^{2n}=\omega^{6m}=(\omega^3)^{2m}=1
\implies \omega^{2n}+\omega^n+1=3\ne0
\implies \omega
x^{2n}+x^n+1=0
n=3m+1,\omega^{2n}+\omega^n+1=\omega^{2(3m+1)}+\omega^{3m+1}+1=\omega^2+\omega+1=0
\implies \omega
x^{2n}+x^n+1=0
\implies (x-\omega)|(x^{2n}+x^n+1)
(x-\omega^2)|(x^{2n}+x^n+1)
(x-\omega)(x-\omega^2)=x^2+x+1\implies (x^2+x+1)|(x^{2n}+x^n+1)
n=3m+2
